fields.question: What are the essential household cleaning supplies?
fields.answer: Essential household cleaning supplies include dusters, squeegees, mops, sponges & scouring pads, brooms, dustpans, scrub brushes, broom & mop handles, and carpet sweepers.

fields.question: What are common household cleaning products?
fields.answer: Common household cleaning products include carpet cleaners, dish detergent & soap, glass & surface cleaners, floor cleaners, oven & grill cleaners, pet odor & stain removers, toilet bowl cleaners, tub & tile cleaners, furniture cleaners & polish, and household disinfectants.

fields.question: What supplies are recommended for business and office cleaning?
fields.answer: Recommended supplies include vacuum cleaners, floor buffers, all-purpose cleaners, glass cleaners, disinfecting wipes, paper towels, microfiber cloths, and sanitizing sprays.

fields.question: What safety precautions should be taken when using cleaning products?
fields.answer: Always read product labels, use gloves, ventilate the area, avoid mixing chemicals, and store cleaning products away from children and pets.

fields.question: What are some eco-friendly alternatives to common cleaning products?
fields.answer: Eco-friendly alternatives include vinegar and baking soda for all-purpose cleaning, castile soap for dishes, lemon juice for stain removal, and biodegradable sponges.

fields.question: What types of recurring cleaning services are available?
fields.answer: Recurring services include weekly or monthly household cleaning, business office cleaning, window washing, carpet cleaning, and deep-cleaning services.

fields.question: How often should you deep clean your home or office?
fields.answer: Deep cleaning should be done at least every 6 months for homes and quarterly for offices to maintain hygiene and cleanliness.

fields.question: What are the benefits of using green cleaning products?
fields.answer: Green cleaning products are safer for the environment, reduce exposure to harmful chemicals, improve indoor air quality, and are often biodegradable.

fields.question: What is the best way to disinfect an office workspace?
fields.answer: Disinfect desks, phones, keyboards, and door handles daily using disinfectant wipes or sprays. Pay attention to shared spaces like conference rooms and break areas.

fields.question: How can I set up a recurring service for my business?
fields.answer: You can set up a recurring service by contacting Clean Services to arrange a custom schedule that fits your business needs, whether it's weekly, bi-weekly, or monthly.
